olem wands/levi potions render this ineffective as well.<br><br>4) Strafe around them and shadow step while their back is turned. A great way of gaining distance from a melee who uses the keyboard. Cons: after you shadow step, the melee can often score hits on you by attacking your ghost (not fun when he double-attacks for 150+ each hit). (Whether or not this changes with a better connection, I don't know.)<br><br>5) (Indoors) Lose your opponent by running through twisted, forked corridors and cast on him through walls. Cons: This is known by players as &quot;LOS exploiting&quot; and is heavily frowned upon.<br><br>6) Run behind a tree and cast. Cons: Doesn't work if he knows which tree you ran behind, and &quot;fooling&quot; your opponent isn't always easy when he's running right behind you and your spells take 4-5 seconds to cast.<br><br>7) Run up a hill and turn around to create a ghost before casting. Cons: This is &quot;hill-bugging&quot;, and like LOS exploiting, it's considered a cheap tactic.<br><br>8) &quot;Step into the nuke.&quot; (Or dot, or lifetap) This refers to casting a spell, running in a circle, and stopping in the exact same place you started casting in order to channel the spell through. (Try it sometime.) Cons: very, very difficult to do, especially if you're levitating and can't use the ground texture as a reference.<br><br>9) Just stand there and try to channel spells like BoD or Vexing (or Draught of Fire if you are a wizard). Cons: extremely dangerous.<br><br>Obviously, none of these tactics are fool-proof. The question I want to ask is, how do *you* do it? What is it that &quot;skilled&quot; casters do to buy time to land spells on melee classes in PvP? Any advice more experienced PvPers might have is appreciated.<br><br>Cerilius D`Nixx<br>54 Necromancer, VZ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/13/02 8:10:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying time to cast</span><hr size=1> Well, the list is fairly extensive. But one tactic that I have found to work as a better alternative to (9) is to move short bits while casting quick spells. The enemy might make a mistake, have connection problems or simply take longer to move so he can hit you then it took you to move.But if you are facing a well equiped, skilled player with good conection then you are basicly stuck with shadowstep and luck as options (or use questionable tactics mentioned). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utinthalastigris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tinthalas Tigris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/13/02 11:27:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying time to cast</span><hr size=1> Well, since this is the wizzy board and the PvP forum *on* the wizzy boared, i'll tell you how to beat everyone.<br><br>Shock of lightning.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/14/02 8:29:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying time to cast</span><hr size=1> Shock of lighting? Wont help you much when fighting a melee, that I asume was the subject of this thread.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/15/02 4:16:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying time to cast</span><hr size=1> Yes please cast shock of lightning as I pierce and bs you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Should be fun...for me when you die. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uauroreakengro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurore Akengro</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/02 5:18:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying time to cast</span><hr size=1> You forgot a VERY important spell: If you have manaskin on, then unless the melee has an interrupt kick / bash you have about 95% chance of channeling a 4.5 sec level 60 spell at level 60, so test it out some at level 54 and you'll be impressed.<br><br>'tanking' a tank is a very bad idea, but what happens is if you are able to get a little distance between you and the tank then you'll have room to try to cast and channel.<br><br>Then the idea is just like a wizard to shadowstep and re skin up if it wears off. Be aware that while you do this chances aer the melee is pumicing off your dots. That's why with a necro I think against a melee open up with a nice pyrocuror (or ignite blood) channel a splurt, either the melee decides to stay there to pumice your dots in which case you can stick pet on him and recast the dots while he pumices, or he chases you and he is taking damage.<br><br>Necros are really good since they have skin spells, shadowstep and also heal spells that you can use on a passing by lvl 1 mob. I play a necro also on RZ and I find they are better than wizards by an enormous margin, unless you want to sit at portals and gank people before they get control.<br><br>Hope this helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utrylun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trylun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/27/02 3:18:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Aurore, any decent Wizard will blow a Necro away.<br><br>-Trylun<br>°Rallos Zek° <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utinthalastigris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tinthalas Tigris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/27/02 2:44:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m